ater segment length of more than two kilometers and one hundred meters wide and connects to Zaslavsky reservoir near the boarding house \"Youth\" and the village Gonoles. <br />However, in the hottest period of the summer there is a big flow of water in the reservoir and thus the water level fell, which naturally influenced the level of water in the rowing channel. This situation precluded the possibility of the training process and competition on the channel. <br /> One of the major shortcomings of the channel, which was on the balance sheet \"Minskvodokanala\" was the presence of a weak flow of water towards the Zaslavsky reservoir, which is also, in turn, ruled out the possibility of international competition and create a level playing field athletes. Faced with a similar problem to address the Minsk City Executive Committee, the main architectural control of Minsk together with the Institute \"Begiprovodhoz\" developed the project of reconstruction of the rowing canal, which would meet the requirements. <br /> In 1995, the Minsk City Executive Committee passed a rowing base in the channel balance to MCIT and Ministry of Communication and, in turn, on balance REPC Aquatics. <br /> Considering the achievements of the Belarusian rowers who started his racing path on the channel in Zaslavl is Olympic champion and world champion E.Karsten, Olympic champion and world champion V.Reneysky, as well as the fact that in the Canoe Sprint in our country 14 Olympic champions from 1960 about 2008. According Rowing many silver and bronze medalists. Multiple world and European champions. Athletes and coaches of the country appealed to the President of the Republic Alexander Lukashenko and chairman of the PP Prokopovich rowing federation with a request to reconstruct the rowing channel in Zaslavl. <br /> Presidential Decree number 454 of 17 July 2006 \"On the reconstruction of the rowing canal Institution\" National Center of Olympic training for rowing \"in Zaslavl.<br /> \" Ministry of Architecture and Construction, the State Committee on Property, Minsk Oblast Executive Committee indicated to provide maximum assistance to the customer (MCIT) in the organization of concurrent engineering construction and design of land use rights, in order to enter in September 2010, the rowing channel in operation year.<br /> Customer advocates the construction of RUE \"Management of Construction Projects of the Ministry of Sports and Tourism of the Republic of Belarus\". General contracting design and construction organizations: JSC \"Minskvodstroy\". <br /> Source of funding: the national budget; means the National Bank of the Republic of Belarus. <br /> The total allotted area of ​​139.27 ha., Including the water surface about 80 hectares. <br /> The task of reconstruction of the canal have been shifted about 1.7 million. M / cu. soil, about 0.7 million. m / cu. concrete embedded in the dam and the dam. <br /> In 2010, put into operation: <br />- Recovery Center <br /> - Administrative building (with the object Catering 44 seats and a dormitory for 72 people, 4 boathouses, three gyms) <br /> - Finishing Tower <br /> - Stands 150, 500 seats <br />- Gas boiler - Network engineering - Landscaping. Track rowing channel bottom width of 135 m. And a depth of 3.5 m. The waters of the channel length of 2,150 m, the length of the approach and the waste of the 45 m and 110 m respectively. 8 and 2 starting backup track width of 13.5 m. <br /> The installation of the electronic system \"Start-Finish\", fully kompyutezitrovannoy, with the conclusion of the information on the display. <br />Hydrotechnical part of the canal was commissioned October 7, 2008. On the ground floor of the office building is strength training room, equipped with exercise machines and free weights projectiles room \"concept\" trainers, \"Falcon\", allowing to simulate rowing on water, rowing basin for rowing 8 seats. Women\'s and men\'s locker rooms. Four hangar for storage of sports boats